Metadata: Conference notes from the California Sea Grant Symposium, Berkeley, California, August 13-14, 1990.

A symposium was held to discuss the approaches, problems, and future development needs associated with rehabilitating and re-qualifying ageing marine structures. The symposium addressed port, coastal, offshore, and ship structures. This document summarizes key results developed from the presentations and discussions held, as well as the results from a questionnaire distributed to participants regarding future workshops and short courses.
